ekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/cbd45ebc.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                    \u003cimg width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"An Xbox controller connected to an iPhone\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/cbd45ebc.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/cbd45ebc.jpg\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n                                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eMicrosoft\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                        \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUntil it\u0026#39;s possible to play Xbox-exclusive games on PC hardware (legally), the other parts of Microsoft\u0026#39;s plans revolve around its cloud gaming service. Between that and the native PC Play Anywhere titles, this \u0026#34;Xbox\u0026#34; handheld could cover most if not all the same library of games on Xbox Series consoles.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003ePersonally, I\u0026#39;m not a fan of cloud gaming, and it\u0026#39;s not practical (or available) everywhere in the world, but it\u0026#39;s a legitimately valuable feature. Given how well (and inexplicably) the PlayStation Portal sold, this is undoubtedly a key part of the overall strategy,\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"microsoft-rsquo-s-open-hardware-strategy-is-a-strength\"\u003e\n                        Microsoftâ€™s Open Hardware Strategy Is a Strength\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                                                        \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/legion-go-s-glacier-white-showing-off-xbox-game-pass.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;Lenovo\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/legion-go-s-glacier-white-showing-off-xbox-game-pass.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/legion-go-s-glacier-white-showing-off-xbox-game-pass.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/legion-go-s-glacier-white-showing-off-xbox-game-pass.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/legion-go-s-glacier-white-showing-off-xbox-game-pass.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/legion-go-s-glacier-white-showing-off-xbox-game-pass.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/legion-go-s-glacier-white-showing-off-xbox-game-pass.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/legion-go-s-glacier-white-showing-off-xbox-game-pass.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/legion-go-s-glacier-white-showing-off-xbox-game-pass.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                    \u003cimg width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Legion Go S glacier white showing off Xbox Game Pass.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/legion-go-s-glacier-white-showing-off-xbox-game-pass.png\" src=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/legion-go-s-glacier-white-showing-off-xbox-game-pass.png\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                        \u003cfigcaption\u003eLenovo\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n                        \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe whole \u0026#34;this is an Xbox\u0026#34; marketing push is clearly a way to reposition Microsoft\u0026#39;s own native hardware as just a minor part of a constellation of products and services with the Xbox brand on it. Xbox isn\u0026#39;t a console, it\u0026#39;s the brand itself now.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eSince Xbox consoles have now consistently sold poorly compared to the competition over multiple generations, partnering with existing hardware makers is a logical move. Just like SteamOS, it looks like the new Windows 11 experience will result in a consistent console-like experience across different devices without the cost and risk of developing bespoke console hardware.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eIt doesn\u0026#39;t have to stop at handheld PCs either. This new approach will work just as well on a desktop PC. Just like Valve\u0026#39;s (possibly returning) Steam Machines, you could put this gaming-focused version of Windows on a desktop PC connected to a TV in your living room and be on your merry way.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n                \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n             